HEADWORD: Cyatholith
<hw>Cy*ath"olith</hw> <pr>(s?-?th"?-l?th)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>ky`aqos</grk> a cup + <ets>-lith</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>A kind of coccolith, which in shape resembles a minute cup widened
at the top, and varies in size from ⟦frac1x6000⟧ to ⟦frac1x8000⟧ of an
inch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cyathophylloid</ent>⟦br⟧
